R Notebook

Loadin the libraries

library(CodeClanData)
library(ggplot2)

Take the data in the dataset qb_revenue_breakdown and make a stacked bar chart showing the sources of revenue across the two years in the dataset.

ggplot(qb_revenue_breakdown) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity")

Make a line chart showing monthly sales of the flagship product - the KwikBit Unit1 - over the last year. This data is inside qb_monthly_sales, but you will need to use subset.

ggplot(subset(qb_monthly_sales, Cashflow == "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales")) +
  aes(x = Date, y = as.integer(Amount)) +
  geom_line()

Make a line chart showing monthly revenue and costs over the last year. This data is also in qb_monthly_sales.

separated_data <- subset(qb_monthly_sales, 
                 qb_monthly_sales$Cashflow == "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales")
cost <- subset(qb_monthly_sales, 
                 qb_monthly_sales$Cashflow == "Cost")
revenue <- subset(qb_monthly_sales, 
                 qb_monthly_sales$Cashflow == "Total Revenue")
separated_data$cost <- cost$Amount
separated_data$revenue <- revenue$Amount
ggplot(separated_data) +
  aes(x = cost, y = revenue) +
  geom_line(colour = "blue") +
  geom_point(colour = "black")

4.2 Potential Personal fitness trackers are a growth industry. One company does not dominate the field. Show annual sales of personal fitness trackers over the last 5 years broken down by company as a ribbon plot (use geom_area). This data is in qb_competitors.

ggplot(qb_competitors) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Company) +
  geom_area(alpha = 0.45)

Now show the sales from the 5 competitors as a line graph. Include an extra layer that shows the data points used to make the lines.

ggplot(qb_competitors) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, colour = Company) +
  geom_line(alpha = 0.45) +
  geom_point()

5 Extension Try out different ways of plotting these three datasets. Which graphs do you think are particularly effective at showing QikBits success?

Plotting sales against revenue:

ggplot(separated_data) +
  aes(x = Amount, y = revenue) +
  geom_line(colour = "blue") +
  geom_point(colour = "black") +
  labs(
    x = "Kwikbit Sales Amount",
    y = "Total Ravenue",
    title = "Progression of the total revenue depending on Kwikbit sales"
  )
